<Issue id="16621" key="FAB-3844" number="3844" project="10002" reporter="wlahti" assignee="wlahti" creator="wlahti" type="10001" summary="Add parameter when creating CallStackError to adjust starting point of callstack" priority="3" resolution="10000" status="6" created="2017-05-11 14:16:39.0" updated="2018-07-20 18:54:14.0" resolutiondate="2017-08-23 13:20:21.0" votes="1" watches="3" workflowId="38473"> <description><! CDATA The error handling framework currently relies on every file importing the error handling package (fabric/common/errors) and making a call similar to: {code:java} errors.ErrorWithCallstack(errors.ChaincodeSupport, errors.BadRequest, "chaincode name not set"){code} Certain packages may wish to wrap this call into their own utility function but not have this utility function displayed in every error callstack.      To accommodate this usage, the error handling framework should provide a parameter to adjust the starting point of the callstack.   For example, the following usage would shift the stack down two lines: {code:java} errors.ErrorWithShiftedCallstack(2, errors.ChaincodeSupport, errors.BadRequest, "chaincode name not set"){code}  ></description> </Issue>
